<collectingCountry id="F3170EBBFFF2FFE498085E28FBE4C314" box="[1045,1139,564,590]" name="Zambia" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Zambia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBF4E2BFFF2FFE49D255E40FDEDC3C4" blockId="40.[264,1323,284,750]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
Etymology. Latin, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0035A8FFF2FFE49E095E40FDF5C32F" authorityName="Scarbrough &amp; Marascia" authorityYear="2003" box="[532,610,604,629]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Ommatius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbus">
<emphasis id="B9749239FFF2FFE49E095E40FDF5C32F" box="[532,610,604,629]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">limbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, meaning border or fringe, referring to the long yellow setae on the legs and tergites 5 and 6.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBF4E2BFFF2FFE49D255EB0FBBEC3B4" blockId="40.[264,1323,284,750]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
Remarks. In addition to the characters in the key, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0035A8FFF2FFE49F605EB0FC79C39F" authorityName="Scarbrough &amp; Marascia" authorityYear="2003" box="[893,1006,684,709]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Ommatius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbus">
<emphasis id="B9749239FFF2FFE49F605EB0FC79C39F" box="[893,1006,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">O. limbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by the large robust, black body, and the 4­6 stout bristles below the fore femur (
<figureCitation id="133B52AEFFF2FFE49FD95EC8FB8BC3B4" box="[964,1052,724,750]" captionStart="FIGURES 21­28" captionStartId="65.[264,382,1754,1778]" captionTargetBox="[277,1313,348,1567]" captionTargetId="figure-98@65.[242,1321,324,1693]" captionTargetPageId="65" captionText="FIGURES 21­28. Right wing of male Ommatius (Pygommatius) spp. 21. O. talus, sp. n.; 22. O. vultus, sp. n.; 23­28. Right fore femur of male Ommatius (Pygommatius) spp. showing arrangement of anteroventral bristles. 23. O. brevicornis Curran; 24. O. grossus, sp. n.; 25. O. limbus, sp. n.; 26. O. litoreus, sp. n.; 27. O. strigiatus, sp. n..; 28. O. vultus, sp. n." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5019049" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5019049/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
